reviewText: This is the epitomy of rock n roll. When you go to Webster's Dictionary and look up rock n roll, it should say "See Led Zeppelin".
Title: Led Zeppelin: Dazed & Confused

reviewText: Led Zeppelin, ... great, as always !!!Led Zeppelin, what was, is now, and always will be.I love watching Jason Bonham in his Dad's shoes.
summary: For my friend --- he loved it.
Title: Led Zeppelin: Dazed & Confused

reviewText: Best Band Evere!!!!!!!!!!  Led Zeppelin is the all time best band ever in my opinion and to see them all together is wonderful.  I was born two decades too late.  I did get to see Robert Plant live and that was an incredible blessing.  I saw them on Letterman recently and it was weird to see Jimmy Page with pure white hair...keep rockin and rollin forever no matter what age!
Title: Led Zeppelin: Dazed & Confused

reviewText: Since I was too young to see Zep in their prime, I am glad that they thought to preserve some of their concerts on film. The next best thing to having seen the concert in person, except for the lack of pot smoke...
Title: Led Zeppelin: Dazed & Confused

reviewText: This is not much in the way of fun and insightful to watch. Once they get to Zeppelin 4, the rest of the program lasts about 10 minutes and mostly covers Bonzo's death and its aftermath. For Zeppelin freaks, it is, I suppose, a little lemon juice on your leg.
summary: Not a Whole Lotta Love for this
Title: Led Zeppelin: Dazed & Confused

reviewText: If you love Led Zeppelin's music you will love this look into the band at its prime.  If you were young when they were young, you will love reliving this time in your life!!!
summary: A Great Look at a Great Group
Title: Led Zeppelin: Dazed & Confused

reviewText: Though it sort of bounces back & forth, it is a great overview & history of Led Zeppelin. I especially like the interviews & footage of Peter Grant (their manager) who was highly instrumental in their success. I'd recommend this to anybody even remotely interested in what Led Zeppelin was all about.
summary: A great history of Led Zeppelin.
Title: Led Zeppelin: Dazed & Confused

reviewText: If you missed Led Zeppelin, where were you?This inexpensive DVD compliments the more polished and more expensive The Song Remains The Same. You should have both.
summary: An Excellent Introduction to the Led Zeppelin Phenomenon
Title: Led Zeppelin: Dazed & Confused
